The team with the most Stanley Cup championships in NHL history is the Montreal Canadiens, a Canadian team based in Montreal, Quebec. However, if we limit the question to American teams, the team with the most Stanley Cup championships is the Detroit Red Wings, based in Detroit, Michigan. The Red Wings have won a total of 11 Stanley Cups, with their most recent championship coming in 2008. The team has a storied history in the NHL, having made the playoffs in 25 consecutive seasons from 1991 to 2016, and is widely regarded as one of the most successful franchises in the league.